(2, 6, 2, '<p>dag landewall</p>', '<p>Senior advisor brands &amp; retail</p>', '<h1>Cave men</h1>\n<h2>in a big data world.</h2>\n<p>Humans are and will always be very social herd animals. We need real life places to meet and yes, shopping is a very much social activity. And like it or not – the most of our shopping is not based on rational needs. We are building our own identity through our choices of products, brands and services. Our aspirations, hopes and desires are the real drivers in most of our consumption, not rational cost/benefit calculations.</p>\n<h3>Make more mistakes. Faster!</h3>\n<p>The winners of tomorrow are thriving on this uncertainty, creating game changing opportunities through a culture of fast and vigilant experimenting. Don’t work? Good, then we know that. Test something else. Work? Good, get it out there – now.</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall is the co-founder of Reactor and has over 30 years of retail and concept development experience.<br> In addition to chair Reactor Retail and Reactor Products he’s advising select corporate clients on retail, concept and brand strategy issues.<br> He’s an expert in developing compelling, consumer relevant and to-the-point brand stories, brand values and personalities.</p>', '<p>+47 952 12 345</p>', '<p><a href="mailto:dag@reactorretail.com">dag@reactorretail.com</a></p>', 4),
