(83, 52, 11, '<p>concept &amp; design direction</p>', '<p>øyvind nystad</p>', '<h1>a shopping experience</h1>\n<h2>is much more than design.</h2>\n<p><span>Too many view design as  the actual shopping experience. To us, design is just one of the dimensions needed to create a successful retail concept. The first dimension is, of course, the product range and how it''s directed, segmented and presented to your customers. The second dimension is how interesting you can make the customers journey through the store, creating interesting sight lines and by changing the rythm in different parts of the store. Why all this is important? As humans, we automatically try to understand and to navigate in a new environment.  We use our natural instincts and all our senses to identify differences and to detect potential opportunities and dangers in our environment. Yes, that''s why humans identify striped patterns faster than all other patterns. Tigers, you know. Therefore, creating a sensory shopping experience including light, sound, shapes and scents helps to dramatise and build your customer''s view of your stores and your brand.</span></p>', '<p>Øyvind Nystad is </p>', '<p>+47 911 78 924</p>', '<p>oyvind@rectorretail.com</p>', 214),
