(116, 6, 30, '<p>brand &amp; concept strategies</p>', '<p>dag landewall</p>', '<h1>get real or be gone</h1>\n<h2>authenticity will be everything</h2>\n<p>Today''s younger consumers, especially the Millenials, are a pretty cynical crowd when it comes to brands and companies, and people and politicians. They are very valuse driven and place great imporatance on authenticity in everything that they relate to in their lives. That can be where they live, the products they buy and the politicians they vote for. Autenticity is of paramount importance to become a successful brand or retailer of tomorrow.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>To be a succesful brand of tomorrow you need elevate the behaiviours that is associated with authenticity;being forthright and clear, stand up for what you believe in and to be transparent. You actually don''t own your brand anymore. The public and your customers decide what hey do wth  Also, showing trust in what the public and your customers will make with your brand   engagement will deliver the essence og authentisict</p>\n<p> </p>', '<p>Dag Landewall, senior brand strategist, is the co-founder of Reactor and has over 30 years of retail and concept development experience. He’s leading the company''s brand strategy work and is also advising select corporate clients on retail, concept and brand strategy issues. He’s an expert in developing compelling, consumer relevant and to-the-point brand stories, brand values and personalities.</p>', '<p>+47 952 12 345</p>', '<p><a href="mailto:dag@reactorretail.com">dag@reactorretail.com</a></p>', 218),
