(135, 52, 19, '<p>concept &amp; design direction</p>', '<p>øyvind nystad</p>', '<h1>human instincts</h1>\n<h2>is king in store design</h2>\n<p><span>Too many view design as  the actual shopping experience. To us, design is just one of the dimensions needed to create a successful retail concept. The first dimension is, of course, the product range and how it''s directed, segmented and presented to your customers. The second dimension is how interesting you can make the customers journey through your store, creating interesting sight lines and by changing the rythm in different areas of the store. Why all this is important? As humans, we automatically try to understand and to navigate in a new environment.  We use our natural instincts and all our senses to identify differences and to detect potential opportunities and dangers in our environment. Therefore, creating a sensory shopping experience including light, sound, shapes and scents helps to dramatise and build your customer''s perception of your store and your brand.</span></p>', '<p>Øyvind Nystad, creative director and co-founder of Reactor and of the most respected retail designers in Scandinavia. With over 25 years of concept development and design work for..</p>', '<p>+47 911 78 924</p>', '<p>oyvind@rectorretail.com</p>', 214),
(136, 52, 20, '<p>concept &amp; design direction</p>', '<p>øyvind nystad</p>', '<h1>natural instinct</h1>\n<h2>is king in store design</h2>\n<p><span>Too many view design as  the actual shopping experience. To us, design is just one of the dimensions needed to create a successful retail concept. The first dimension is, of course, the product range and how it''s directed, segmented and presented to your customers. The second dimension is how interesting you can make the customers journey through your store, creating interesting sight lines and by changing the rythm in different areas of the store. Why all this is important? As humans, we automatically try to understand and to navigate in a new environment.  We use our natural instincts and all our senses to identify differences and to detect potential opportunities and dangers in our environment. Therefore, creating a sensory shopping experience including light, sound, shapes and scents helps to dramatise and build your customer''s perception of your store and your brand.</span></p>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Øyvind Nystad, creative director and co-founder of Reactor. More than 25 years of concept development and design work for some of the worlds most respected brands has made Øyvind one of the most respected retail designers in Europe. </p>', '<p>+47 911 78 924</p>', '<p>oyvind@rectorretail.com</p>', 214),
(137, 83, 6, '<p>retail art direction</p>', '<p>ann-catrin friborg</p>', '<h1>a reason to visit</h1>\n<h2>a reason to stay  </h2>\n<p>The perfect store, an artistic vision, the ultimate design, filled with dreams to inspire, incite and entertain. But a beautiful shopping experience is not enough. For a store to be successful the retail design must express the soul of the brand-that is the brand´s values and strength. Striking the right balance among the products,  communication, design, architecture and education is the only way to achieve this goal. As an retail designer, you need a unique mix of elements for each projects, because every brands develops differently. Ultimate shopping experience is a place driven by passion and experience. You can have a fantastically designed store, but if the owners and staff aren´t  fully behind it, it will never work. Fantastic opportunities exist for imaginative retailers.</p>', '<p>Ann-Catrin...</p>', '<p>+47   </p>', '<p>acf@</p>', 217),
