(214, 83, 19, '<p>retail art direction</p>', '<p>ann-catrin friborg</p>', '<h1>a reason to visit</h1>\n<h2>and a reason to stay</h2>\n<p>Occasionally one feels welcome just by going into a room. At first, it is difficult to understand why. Then you understand that somebody has twisted and turned every detail and in so doing has created an integrated whole. The parts play together while they also each work individually to make the experience greater. A style is found here that you would like to experience over and over. It is design for your senses. It is a feeling that gives inspiration and a positive shopping experience. It is a place where you want to spend time in, a place you want to come back to. We think that as a home reflects the personality of the owner, a store should also reflect the personality of your company and your brand. After all, for a retailer – the store is the brand itself. Your approach should thus be to create a holistic shopping experience that hopefully answers the most important question for anyone in retail: why should somebody come to my store?</p>', '<p>Ann-Catrin Friborg, Retail Art Director, joined Reactor in 2003 after a 10-year international store design career with IKEA. She has led several major concept development projects and she is an expert in creating strong, differentiating and coherent retail experiences.</p>', '<p>(+47)  97 68 38 52 </p>', '<p>ancf@reactorretail.com</p>', 258),
