(273, 78, 31, '<p>brand idenity design</p>', '<p>hilde steen aamodt</p>', '<h1>gold diggers</h1>\n<p>Excellent visual expressions of brands are mostly based on the company''s own DNA and are able to tell the history, aspirations and vision of the brand in a condensed form.</p>\n<p>I believe in cultivating the client company''s personal traits, characteristics and values to its full potential and prefer to creating the identity from within, based on visual translations of strategic insights rather than to base it on design trends. My experience is that this approach results in extended longlivety for the brand and that it also will generate greater pride and internal ownership. Also, idenitites created from within are often perceived as more unique and trustworthy in the marketplace.</p>\n<p>Therefore our approach is that every company and brand has a golden ore to be discovered - and our job is to find that ore and make sustainable brandwork out of it.</p>', '<p>Hilde Steen Aamodt, Senior Graphic Designer, is a well experienced graphic designer. In addition to creating commercially successful identities, she creates complete design programs and guidelines, brand &amp; in-store communication, editorial design and advertising. Hilde is behind the visual expression for a wide range of brand designs i.e. Nille, Jøtul, Match, Voice, Regatta, Printz, Lefdal, Eurosko, Gyldendal, Tiden and Miles.</p>\n<p>Her work has been awarded with The Award for Design Excellence.</p>', '<p>+47 900 39 019</p>', '<p>hilde@reactorretail.com</p>', 260),
(274, 6, 81, '<p>brand &amp; concept strategies</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall</p>', '<h1>from vice to virtues</h1>\n<h2>a brand needs character</h2>\n<p>It''s not a coincidence that many of the world''s most successful brands have a founder with a strong personality that also becomes the company''s brand personality. IKEA is Ingvar Kamprad and Apple is (still) Steve Jobs. But that doesn''t mean companies without a charismatic founder cannot develop a strong, relevant and likeble character. Every single company has its own history with its unique traits, which add up to the company''s personality.</p>\n<p>I believe that a brand first of all should be authentic and true to its own culture. Instead of trying to become what you are not - be clear about what you really are. Identify and describe your virtues and define the consequences of being true to them. Then your brand gets authenticity and character, which is paramount for creating excellent designs and concepts.  </p>', '<p>Dag Landewall, Senior Brand Strategist, is the co-founder of Reactor and has over 30 years of retail and concept development experience. He leads the company''s brand strategy work and creates compelling, consumer-relevant and to-the-point brand stories and personalities for select corporate clients.</p>', '<p>+47 952 12 345</p>', '<p><a href="mailto:dag@reactorretail.com">dag@reactorretail.com</a></p>', 257),
(275, 80, 30, '<p>retail tender management &amp; roll-outs</p>', '<p>erik huseby</p>', '<h1>big ideas </h1>\n<h2>into the real world</h2>\n<p>In the disruptive and unpredictable market of today, many great ideas become irrelevant before they reach the marketplace. For many large companies it has proved difficult to adjust their concept development and implementation processes to this new reality.</p>\n<p>However, my experience is that it''s possible to speed up the time used between the creation of the next big thing and it''s first meeting with real customers.</p>\n<p>Our approach is to prepare the concept for a roll-out right from the start.  Also, concept elements should be prototyped as they are developed at the drawingtable. Finnaly, a successful procurement process require in-depth knowledge about the shop-fitting market and production methods. A proffesionally made  retail tender management process normally account for  20 - 30% investment savings. Talk to me, and I''ll tell you how.</p>', '<p>Erik Huseby, Managing Director of Reactor Products, our implementation arm, leads our work with bringing the concepts we create into the real world, through sourcing, piloting and roll-out management. Erik has over 20 years expertise in his field and is a leading shop fitting authority and manages tender and hardware sourcing processes for a large number of our clients.   </p>', '<p>(+47) 916 86 244</p>', '<p>erik@reactorretail.com</p>', 264),
