(289, 79, 27, '<p>brand marketing</p>', '<p>inger guttormsen </p>', '<h1>retailers</h1>\n<h2>love strong brands </h2>\n<p>The huge rise of private labels has fundamentally changed market power in recent years, from industry big brands and towards retailers.  However, something got lost in the fight as very few retailer private labels have the brand power to shoulder the role of being a category captain. And without a strong category captain brand, it is difficult for a retailer to become a preferred category destination. A soft drink department without Coke, barbecue department without Weber or kitchen appliances without Miele does not resonate well with consumers.</p>\n<p>Wise retailers thus know that they need strong brands to build category authority. So if you own a good industry brand, take a broader view on how you can help retailers transform categories into destinations, creating interesting and inspiring shopping experences that also make customers connect emotionally with your brand and your products. This lets you create a true win-win relationship for both the retailer and your brand.</p>', '<p>Inger Guttormsen joined Reactor in 2012 and is the latest expert to join the advisory team. She has over 10 years of professional experience, ranging from introducing the L''loreal brand in Norway to managing the Nike retail brand presentation. Inger is advising select brand clients on how to create strong in-store brand presentations that resonate well with retailers and consumers while also meeting the brand''s strategic objectives.</p>', '<p>(+ 47) 924 91 600</p>', '<p>inger@reactorretail.com</p>', 263);
