(303, 6, 88, '<p>brand &amp; concept strategies</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall</p>', '<h1>get some character</h1>\n<h2>brands need character</h2>\n<p>It is no coincidence that many of the world''s most successful brands have a founder with a strong personality who also becomes the company''s brand personality. IKEA is Ingvar Kamprad and Apple is (still) Steve Jobs. But that does not mean companies without a charismatic founder cannot develop a strong, relevant and likeble character. Every single company has its own history with its unique traits that add up to the company''s personality.</p>\n<p>I believe that a brand first of all should be authentic and true to its own culture. Instead of trying to become what you are not - be clear about what you really are. Identify your virtues and be true to them. Then your brand acquires authenticity and character, which is paramount for creating an emotional and lasting connection between your brand and the consumers.</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall, Senior Brand Strategist, is the co-founder of Reactor and has over 30 years of retail and concept development experience. He leads the company''s brand strategy work and creates compelling, consumer-relevant and to-the-point brand stories and personalities for select corporate clients.</p>', '<p>(+47) 952 12 345</p>', '<p><a href="mailto:dag@reactorretail.com">dag@reactorretail.com</a></p>', 257),
