(320, 78, 34, '<p>brand idenity design</p>', '<p>hilde steen aamodt</p>', '<h1>gold diggers</h1>\n<p>Excellent visual expressions of brands are mostly based on the company''s own DNA and are able to tell the history, aspirations and vision of the brand in a condensed form.</p>\n<p>I believe in cultivating the client company''s personal traits, characteristics and values to its full potential and prefer creating the identity from within, based on visual translations of strategic insights rather than to base it on design trends. My experience is that this approach results in extended longevity for the brand and that it also generates greater pride and internal ownership. In addition, idenitites created from within are often perceived as more unique and trustworthy in the marketplace.</p>\n<p>Consequently, our approach is that every company and brand possesses gold ore waiting to be discovered - and our job is to find that ore and make sustainable brandwork out of it.</p>', '<p>Hilde Steen Aamodt, Senior Graphic Designer, is a highly experienced graphic designer. In addition to creating commercially successful identities,</p>\n<p>she creates complete design programs and guidelines, brand &amp; in-store communication, editorial design and advertising. Hilde is behind the visual expression for a wide range of brand designs i.e. Nille, Jøtul, Match, Voice, Regatta, Printz, Lefdal, Eurosko, Gyldendal, Tiden and Miles.</p>\n<p>Her work has been awarded The Award for Design Excellence.</p>', '<p>(+47) 900 39 019</p>', '<p>hilde@reactorretail.com</p>', 260),
(321, 80, 32, '<p>retail tender management &amp; roll-outs</p>', '<p>erik huseby</p>', '<h1>big ideas </h1>\n<h2>into the real world</h2>\n<p>In the disruptive and unpredictable market of today, many great ideas become irrelevant before they reach the marketplace. For many large companies it has proved difficult to adjust their concept development and implementation processes to this new reality.</p>\n<p>However, my experience is that it is possible to shorten the interval between the creation of the next big thing and its first encounter with real customers.</p>\n<p>Our approach is to prepare a concept for roll-out right from the start.  Also, concept elements should be prototyped as they are developed at the drawing table. Finally, a successful procurement process requires in-depth knowledge of the shop-fitting market and production methods. A professionally done retail tender management process normally accounts for 20 - 30% investment savings. Talk to me, and I will tell you how.</p>', '<p>Erik Huseby, Managing Director of Reactor Products, our implementation arm, leads our work with bringing the concepts we create into the real world,</p>\n<p>through sourcing, piloting and roll-out management. Erik has over 20 years of expertise in his field and is a leading shop-fitting authority and manages tender and hardware sourcing processes for a large number of our clients.   </p>', '<p>(+47) 916 86 244</p>', '<p>erik@reactorretail.com</p>', 264),
