(332, 78, 35, '<p>brand idenity design</p>', '<p>hilde steen aamodt</p>', '<h1>gold diggers</h1>\n<p>Excellent visual expressions of brands are mostly based on the company''s own DNA and are able to tell the history, aspirations and vision of the brand in a condensed form.</p>\n<p>I believe in cultivating the client company''s personal traits, characteristics and values to its full potential and prefer creating the identity from within, based on visual translations of strategic insights rather than to base it on design trends. My experience is that this approach results in extended longevity for the brand and that it also generates greater pride and internal ownership. In addition, idenitites created from within are often perceived as more unique and trustworthy in the marketplace. Consequently, our approach is that every company and brand possesses gold ore waiting to be discovered - and our job is to find that ore and make sustainable brandwork out of it.</p>', '<p>Hilde Steen Aamodt, Senior Graphic Designer, is a highly experienced graphic designer. In addition to creating commercially successful identities,</p>\n<p>she creates complete design programs and guidelines, brand &amp; in-store communication, editorial design and advertising. Hilde is behind the visual expression for a wide range of brand designs i.e. Nille, Jøtul, Match, Voice, Regatta, Printz, Lefdal, Eurosko, Gyldendal, Tiden and Miles.</p>\n<p>Her work has been awarded The Award for Design Excellence.</p>', '<p>(+47) 900 39 019</p>', '<p>hilde@reactorretail.com</p>', 260),
(333, 78, 36, '<p>brand idenity design</p>', '<p>hilde steen aamodt</p>', '<h1>gold diggers</h1>\n<p>Excellent visual expressions of brands are mostly based on the company''s own DNA and are able to tell the history, aspirations and vision of the brand in a condensed form. I believe in cultivating the client company''s personal traits, characteristics and values to its full potential and prefer creating the identity from within, based on visual translations of strategic insights rather than to base it on design trends. My experience is that this approach results in extended longevity for the brand and that it also generates greater pride and internal ownership. In addition, idenitites created from within are often perceived as more unique and trustworthy in the marketplace. Consequently, our approach is that every company and brand possesses gold ore waiting to be discovered - and our job is to find that ore and make sustainable brandwork out of it.</p>', '<p>Hilde Steen Aamodt, Senior Graphic Designer, is a highly experienced graphic designer. In addition to creating commercially successful identities,</p>\n<p>she creates complete design programs and guidelines, brand &amp; in-store communication, editorial design and advertising. Hilde is behind the visual expression for a wide range of brand designs i.e. Nille, Jøtul, Match, Voice, Regatta, Printz, Lefdal, Eurosko, Gyldendal, Tiden and Miles.</p>\n<p>Her work has been awarded The Award for Design Excellence.</p>', '<p>(+47) 900 39 019</p>', '<p>hilde@reactorretail.com</p>', 260),
(334, 78, 37, '<p>brand idenity design</p>', '<p>hilde steen aamodt</p>', '<h1>gold diggers</h1>\n<p>Excellent visual expressions of brands are mostly based on the company''s own DNA and are able to tell the history, aspirations and vision of the brand in a condensed form. I believe in cultivating the client company''s personal traits, characteristics and values to its full potential and prefer creating the identity from within, based on visual translations of strategic insights rather than to base it on design trends. My experience is that this approach results in extended longevity for the brand and that it also generates greater pride and internal ownership. In addition, idenitites created from within are often perceived as more unique and trustworthy in the marketplace. Consequently, our approach is that every company and brand possesses gold ore waiting to be discovered - and our job is to find that ore and make sustainable brandwork out of it.</p>', '<p>Hilde Steen Aamodt, Senior Graphic Designer, is a highly experienced graphic designer. In addition to creating commercially successful identities, she creates complete design programs and guidelines, brand &amp; in-store communication, editorial design and advertising. Hilde is behind the visual expression for a wide range of brand designs i.e. Nille, Jøtul, Match, Voice, Regatta, Printz, Lefdal, Eurosko, Gyldendal, Tiden and Miles. Her work has been awarded The Award for Design Excellence.</p>', '<p>(+47) 900 39 019</p>', '<p>hilde@reactorretail.com</p>', 260),
(335, 6, 91, '<p>brand &amp; concept strategies</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall</p>', '<h1>get some character</h1>\n<p>It is no coincidence that many of the world''s most successful brands have a founder with a strong personality who also becomes the company''s brand personality. IKEA is Ingvar Kamprad and Apple is (still) Steve Jobs. But that does not mean companies without a charismatic founder cannot develop a strong, relevant and likeble character. Every single company has its own history with its unique traits that add up to the company''s personality.</p>\n<p>I believe that a brand first of all should be authentic and true to its own culture. Instead of trying to become what you are not - be clear about what you really are. Identify your virtues and be true to them. Then your brand acquires authenticity and character, which is paramount for creating an emotional and lasting connection between your brand and the consumers.</p>', '<p>Dag Landewall, Senior Brand Strategist, is the co-founder of Reactor and has over 30 years of retail and concept development experience. He leads the company''s brand strategy work and creates compelling, consumer-relevant and to-the-point brand stories and personalities for select corporate clients.</p>', '<p>(+47) 952 12 345</p>', '<p><a href="mailto:dag@reactorretail.com">dag@reactorretail.com</a></p>', 257),
(336, 79, 36, '<p>brand marketing</p>', '<p>inger guttormsen </p>', '<h1>creating win-wins</h1>\n<p>The huge rise of private labels has fundamentally changed market power in recent years, from big brands towards retailers private labels. However, something got lost in the fight as very few retailer private labels have the brand power to shoulder the role of being a category captain. And without a strong category captain brand, it is difficult for a retailer to become a preferred category destination. A soft drink department without Coke, barbecue department without Weber or kitchen appliances without Miele does not resonate well with consumers. Wise retailers thus know that they need strong brands to build category authority. So if you own a good industry brand, take a broader view on how you can help retailers transform categories into destinations, creating interesting and inspiring shopping experences that also make customers connect emotionally with your brand and your products. This lets you create a true win-win relationship for both the retailer and your brand.</p>', '<p>Inger Guttormsen joined Reactor in 2012 and is the latest expert to join our advisory team. She has over 10 years of professional experience,</p>\n<p>ranging from building strong brands through marketing positions at L''Oréal, to managing the Nike retail brand strategy and implementation within the Norwegian sport industry. Inger is advicing select brand clients on how to create strong instore brand presentations that resonate well</p>\n<p>among retailers and consumers while meeting the brand''s strategic objectives.</p>', '<p>(+ 47) 924 91 600</p>', '<p>inger@reactorretail.com</p>', 263),
