(46, 87, 4, '<p>Kronans was founded in Sweden in 1907 and are now operating over 200 pharmacies across Sweden.</p>\n<h1>two stores in one</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p style="text-align: justify;">It’s not only airports which capitalize on locations where people are on their way. Major commuter hubs does the same and Stockholm Central Station is no exception in trying to offer travelers the convenience of shopping on the go. The Kronan store has a unique but complicated location at the subway turnstiles as it''s accessible from both sides of the stiles. </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We created two stores in one targeting the different mind-set and shopping patterns on the two sides of the stiles; The store inside the stiles is designed for the customer with very limited time to use; low gondolas for quick overview and products clearly displayed in top list products clearly displayed. The store outside the stiles is designed for the customer with more time to use. It has a much wider product range and a store design that invites the customer to browse.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This location also offer a drop-box/pick up point for prescriptions for additional speed and convenience. Hand in the prescription on your way to work – pick your medicines up on your way home. </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We also sourced and coordinated all production and implementation of store fittings, lighting, signage, graphics and displays, securing that everything worked smoothly from day 1.</p>', '<p>It’s not only airports which capitalize on locations where people are on their way. Major commuter hubs does the same and Stockholm Central Station is no exception in trying to offer travelers the convenience of shopping on the go. The Kronan store has a unique but complicated location at the subway turnstiles as it''s accessible from both sides of the stiles. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We created two stores in one targeting the different mind-set and shopping patterns on the two sides of the stiles; The store inside the stiles is designed for the customer with very limited time to use; low gondolas for quick overview and products clearly displayed in top list products clearly displayed. The store outside the stiles is designed for the customer with more time to use. It has a much wider product range and a store design that invites the customer to browse.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>This location also offer a drop-box/pick up point for prescriptions for additional speed and convenience. Hand in the prescription on your way to work – pick your medicines up on your way home. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We also sourced and coordinated all production and implementation of store fittings, lighting, signage, graphics and displays, securing that everything worked smoothly from day 1.</p>', 0),
