(64, 91, 5, '<h5>Graphic Designer Therese Skjenken (left) working out the design details for Miles, the new brand of fuel for Statoil, together with Project Manager Hedi Nielsen (right). The Miles design program will be applied at over 50 different pumps and ranging.</h5>\n<h1>miles for statoil</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p><span>It seemed like a perfect idea at the time: Letting the banking customers make all of the work directly on the web. Faster and more convenient for the customers - major efficiency gains for the banks. Accordingly, the major banks shut down a  large number of their branches. Now everybody happy? Not quite. Well, this is a story you might have heard before, but the major banks focused to fight eachother and simply underestimated the threath from outside the banking sector. In addition, they didn''t see what mobile pay technologies whould do to them either. It''s estimated that non-banks will increase their market share to 15% in 2020. It was 1,5 % in 2014. In addition, the virtualization of the banking sector made the banks more anonymous and increasingly viewed, by the public, as arrogant and less customer focused. After a few years struggling to develop a new real world interaction with their customers, DNB in april 2014 approached Reactor Retail for advice.</span></p>', '<p><span>So what does it take for a bank to become likeble, relevant and useful to todays consumers? Our approach is that</span></p>', 0),
