(74, 91, 15, '<h5><span>DNB financial advisor Hanna Folkvord speaks with customer Ingvild U. Halvorsen in the new DNB counter-less pilot store in Oslo. photograph by Signe Dons. Source: Aftenposten.</span></h5>\n<h1>dnb goes retail</h1>\n<h6>By Inger Guttormsen</h6>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span>It seemed like a perfect idea at the time: Letting the banking customers make all of the work directly on the web. Faster and more convenient for the customers - major efficiency gains for the banks. Accordingly, the major banks shut down a  large number of their branches. Now everybody happy?</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Not quite. Well, this is a story you might have heard before from other sectors, but the major banks focused to fight eachother and simply underestimated the threath from outside the banking sector. In addition, they didn''t see what mobile pay technologies whould do to them either. It''s estimated that non-banks will increase their banking market share to 15% in 2020. It was 1,5 % in 2014. In addition, the virtualization of the banking sector made the banks more anonymous and increasingly viewed, by the public, as arrogant and less customer focused.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> After a few years struggling to develop a new real world interaction with their customers, DNB in april 2014 approached Reactor Retail for advice.</p>', '<p><span>So what does it take for a bank to become likeble, relevant and useful to todays consumers? Our approach is that while technology will drive convenience and efficiency, personal interaction and physical meeting places will drive trust. And in banking - trust is perhaps the paramount virtue for anyone with major ambitions.</span></p>\n<p><span>Retailizing the bank: We created a a people oriented banking shopping experience that remove physical barriers between customers and staff. The concept aim to bring the bank and it''s customers on a partnership level, without the traditional banking powerdressing attitude. It makes people relax and inspire to dialogue and partnership. Retailing methology is used for creating an interesting and surprising shopping experience through the use of furniture design, lighting, visual merchnadising tehniques, instore communcation and  product packaging. </span></p>\n<p><span>The first pilot is opened up at the DNB HQ in Oslo and the second will open up in a shopping center location in Oslo in April 2015.</span></p>', 0),
