(102, 101, 4, '<h5>The Statoil Highway Concept gave Statoil the 2012 Convenience Retailer of The Year Award.  </h5>\n<h1>Highway Gold</h1>\n<h6>By Dag Landewall</h6>', '<p>The judging panel praised the calibre of entries and admitted it was severely tested in drawing up this year’s shortlist. Stephanie Rice, founder of Rice Retail Marketing, said: “I think the calibre of entries is excellent. I think there are some real examples of innovation.”Several of the panel commented that it was a close call between all of this year’s candidates. For example, Ramon Kuijpers, international key accounts manager, Reemtsma Cigarettenfabriken Gmbh, an Imperial Tobacco Group company, said: “The differences between the top six retailers on my shortlist are again quite small, given the high quality of entries.”</p>\n<p>Joe Bona, president, retail division, CBX, agreed. “There was a close one, two and three; and a different lead scorer in each of the seven criteria making it somewhat challenging to find a standout winner,” he said. Bona rated Statoil Fuel &amp; Retail, in particular. Its pilot highway format store in Minnesund, Norway, is meeting customer needs by providing clustered convenience concepts. Statoil Fuel &amp; Retail has researched the market in order to develop the site and has taken on board the reasons its customers stop at highway locations. </p>', '<p>The Minnesund site design has been carefully thought through and features separate a forecourt area and shop. In the shop, the layout is divided into distinct departments including self-serve coffee, bread and bakery, a fresh food offer, salad bar, convenience offer and services. The food offer is tailored to the time of day with breakfast, lunch and dinner options available. Since launch, sales and customer numbers at the Minnesund forecourt are reported to be outperforming average highway locations with food sales significantly stronger than other sites. Rice also praised Statoil for its understanding of the customer mission, which she said has translated into a welcoming and attractive roadside offer. Finally the judges choosed Statoil and the new highway concept created by Reactor Retail as the winner of the 2012 Convenience Retailer of the Year Award.</p>', 0),
