(196, 85, 21, '<h5 style="text-align: justify;"><span>Football-obsessed teens think-act-play football 24/7, and want their style to express their passion.</span>  </h5>\n<h1>nike football 24/7</h1>\n<h6>By Inger Guttormsen</h6>', '<p style="text-align: left;">Under the mission “Bring inspiration and innovation to every athlete in the world” – Nike continues to strengthen their retail position in Europe by launching a brand new football concept.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Niketown meets torshov sport. Torshov Sport, one of the oldest and most competent sport retailers in Oslo, has products for everyone whether you are competing, training or hanging out with your friends. Football-obsessed teens think-act-play football 24/7, and want their style to express their passion.</p>', '<p style="text-align: left;">Based on the Nike football global guidelines, we developed an in-store plan with custom-made solutions for fixtures, displays, campaign areas and service desks. </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">The retail concept developed for and implemented at two Torshov Sport locations in Oslo are the first concept pilots in Europe.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Both stores are performing very well, and have contributed to strengthening the Nike football brand in the Norwegian market.</p>', 221),
(197, 96, 12, '<h5>Our Chef Nana prepares the daily lunch</h5>\n<h1>food for thought</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The daily life at Reactor can be very challenging and is not for the faint hearted. In the early years of the company that also negatively affected our eating habits. In 2009 we decided to quit our bad eating habits and instead offering our emloyees the best lunch in the country, every day. After a thorough recruitment process we where happy to employ our own profesjonal chef; Ning</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The result was astonishing; Not only could we sit down every day and enjoy a delicious meal, all made with love and pride and from the best and  fresh ingredients avaiable.</span></p>', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The lunch quickly raised to the highlight of the working day, </span></p>', 270),
(198, 96, 13, '<h5>Our chef and the most popular employee; Wanassanan Ledrod, prepares the daily lunch at the studio.</h5>\n<h1>food for thought</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The daily life at Reactor can be very challenging and is not for the faint hearted. In the early years of the company that also negatively affected our eating habits. In 2009 we decided to quit our bad eating habits and instead offering our emloyees the best lunch in the country, every day. After a thorough recruitment process we where happy to employ our own professional chef Wanassanan Ledrod.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The result was astonishing; Not only could we sit down every day and enjoy a delicious meal, all made with love and pride and from the best and  fresh ingredients avaiable.</span></p>', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The lunch quickly raised to the highlight of the working day and the positive food experience spread an increasing good mood around the studio. Creativity and productivity increased and the rumour about the fantastic lunch started to spread around our clients, resulting in increasing number of requests of meeting times suspisiosly close to noon.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span>The largest surprise was however that the net cost for lunch in our company decresed in comparsion with the period when we handled our lunch ourselves. Premade or processed industrial food are far more expensive than letting a professional chef source the best fresh ingredients around and then prepare the meal from sctratch. </span></p>', 270),
