(218, 97, 7, '<h5>Astrid Landewall is a trained and experienced personal coach and physiotherapist</h5>\n<h1>it simply must work</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p style="text-align: left;">Developing and implementing a new retail concept is a major undertaking with major investments connected to from design and communication to hardware and multistore implementation. In many cases it also means that sales staff will be required to performe their daly tasks in a new manner. The new concept will include new sales tools and sales staff find themselves in a new working environment and in a concep new powerful salestools planned for an improved dialougue with customers but also new physical, sit stand up, replenish. </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">In our experience, there are two areas which is crucial for commercial success when implementing a new concept. First, the extend which sales staff successfully quickly can adapt to a new sales environment and learn to use their new sales tools is absolutely crucial for commercial success. </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>', '<p style="text-align: left;">It is not only airports that capitalize on locations where people are going places. Major commuter hubs do the same, and Stockholm Central Station is no exception in trying to offer travelers the convenience of shopping on the go. The Kronan store has a unique but complicated location at the subway turnstiles because it is accessible from both sides of the turnstiles. </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">We created two stores in one, targeting the different mindsets and shopping patterns on the two sides of the turnstiles. The store inside the turnstiles is designed for customers with very limited time to spend - low gondolas for quick overviews and with best-selling products clearly displayed.</p>', 271),
