(243, 110, 2, NULL, '<p>Kronans Droghandel began in 1907 as a distributor of medicines. Today, Kronans is one of the largest chains in Sweden, with over 200 pharmacies.</p>\n<p>In connection with its merger with the MedStop pharmacy chain in 2013, it became clear that the previous identity and concept for Kronans Droghandel no longer was functional for communications or commercially. In order to facilitate the potential of the merger to be unlocked, a new identity and design needed to be developed and implemented in both pharmacy networks.</p>', '<p>In consultation with Kronans, Reactor developed a strategy to leverage the momentum from the takeover of MedStop and use it as a driver to develop and implement a new identity and new concept in two nation-wide chains simultaneously.</p>\n<p>Reactor was responsible for the development and design of a new identity, a new logotype and a new communications program as well as applications that were implemented in the two chains in connection with the merger.</p>', 0),
(244, 110, 3, '<h5>Merging two chains </h5>\n<h1>major merger</h1>\n<h6>By Øyvind Nystad</h6>', '<p>Kronans Droghandel began in 1907 as a distributor of medicines. Today, Kronans is one of the largest chains in Sweden, with over 200 pharmacies.</p>\n<p>In connection with its merger with the MedStop pharmacy chain in 2013, it became clear that the previous identity and concept for Kronans Droghandel no longer was functional for communications or commercially. In order to facilitate the potential of the merger to be unlocked, a new identity and design needed to be developed and implemented in both pharmacy networks.</p>', '<p>In consultation with Kronans, Reactor developed a strategy to leverage the momentum from the takeover of MedStop and use it as a driver to develop and implement a new identity and new concept in two nation-wide chains simultaneously.</p>\n<p>Reactor was responsible for the development and design of a new identity, a new logotype and a new communications program as well as applications that were implemented in the two chains in connection with the merger.</p>', 0);
